FT  04 JUN 92 / Observer: Ill met
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
However unlucky it may be to re-name a ship, the Royal Navy must be
considering doing just that to one of its Oberon-class submarines.
With the world's top admirals assembled to watch the RN's Sea Days exercises
 -a showpiece for the efficiency of British naval equipment - the vessel
collided with a container ship while surfacing in the fog-bound Channel.
Although neither was badly damaged, and there were no casualties, the
submarine apparently came off worst.
Its name? HMS Opportune.
