<HEADLINE>
FT  03 JUN 92 / Silver tarnished
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SOTHEBY'S had a very disappointing silver sale in London yesterday. It
totalled Pounds 574,695 but was almost 62 per cent unsold, mainly because
the most important lot, a soup tureen made in 1736 by Paul de Lamerie,
failed to find a buyer.
Sotheby's was hoping for bids in excess of Pounds 750,000 for the
rococo-styled tureen but it was bought in at Pounds 650,000.
</TEXT>
