FT  03 JUN 92 / Parliament and Politics: TGWU to back Smith and Beckett
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE executive of the TGWU general union yesterday decided to back Mr John
Smith and Mrs Margaret Beckett for the leadership and deputy leadership of
the Labour party.
The union holds the biggest single block of Labour's electoral college, with
8 per cent of the votes, nearly one quarter of the 40 per cent union vote.
The shadow chief secretary has recently faced a challenge from Mr John
Prescott, shadow transport secretary.
Mr Prescott, who has been defending Labour's traditional links with the
unions, has won endorsement from Nupe, the public services union, and GPMU,
the print union.
But the Beckett camp was last night pointing out that Mrs Beckett had also
won the endorsement of the Rhondda constituency in south Wales, a
traditional Labour stronghold.
Mr Gordon Brown, Mrs Beckett's campaign manager, said that she was already
leading among MPs, and that her campaign had 'a strong momentum in the
constituency parties and amongst trade unionists.
'Her campaign is uniting the party,' he claimed.
Branches covering about 25 per cent of the TGWU's membership responded to
the union's consultation exercise over the leadership. Mr Smith won about 83
per cent support for the leadership. In the deputy race Mrs Beckett won 46
per cent, Mr Prescott 39 per cent and Mr Gould 15 per cent.
</TEXT>
