decide to open up Bell Canada's monopoly of domestic long-distance telephone
traffic in eastern Canada. 'If competition is the name of the game, then
let's have it,' said Mr Lynton Wilson, BCE president.
Several groups want to compete with Bell Canada in the long-distance market,
including Unitel, owned by Rogers Communications, and Canadian Pacific.
